In article <2rvojs$src@jac.zko.dec.com> edp@rusure.enet.dec.com writes:
>Okay, so there's a version of PGP built using RSAREF or whatever library
>is sanctioned by RSADSI and/or PKP.  But as long as RSADSI and PKP are
>allowing people to use the algorithm (or patented system or other legal
>technicality) for free in the library, why should they care whether
>people use the same algorithm (or whatever) in code that somebody else
>wrote?

Probably because if anyone's using RSA, they want them to be
using RSA Inc.'s RSA.  Follow-ups to alt.security.pgp

